parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Continuously Variable Transmission (CVT) can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or jerk while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates while accelerating
jerks intermittently
loses motive power
stalls
or shuts off while driving
and may display warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, which can obstruct the driver's view and lead to accidents.
symptoms: The hood flies open while driving
causing damage to the windshield and potentially obstructing the driver's view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shifter assembly can cause the gear shift lever to fail to move out of park, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The gear shift lever fails to move out of park
or the vehicle hesitates while shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the engine control module can cause the vehicle to lose power while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power while accelerating
and may display warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag sensor can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light is illuminated on the dashboard
the passenger airbag light is on even when someone is sitting in the seat
the airbag sensor is not detecting occupants correctly
and the airbag may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, obstructing the driver's view and increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: The hood suddenly opens while driving
compromising front visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Dim Headlights due to Delamination of Reflective Materials
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dim headlights can cause accidents or near-misses, especially at night, as the driver may not be able to see the road or other vehicles, pedestrians, or obstacles.
symptoms: The headlights are extremely dim
making it difficult to see while driving at night
even with high beams on. The dimness can be gradual
and the headlights may appear to be functioning normally during the day.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension control arm can cause loss of control, accidents, and injury.
symptoms: The vehicle may vibrate
shake
or pull to one side while driving. The rear tire may be misaligned
and the wheel may be leaning inward.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the rear subframe can cause loss of control, accidents, and injury.
symptoms: The vehicle may vibrate
shake
or pull to one side while driving. The rear tire may be misaligned
and the wheel may be leaning inward.
